From Lee Owen Subject Re WANTED Info on Dedicated X Server Kernel for Series If anyone has any information about the existence or location of a dedicated X server kernel for the please send I am trying to put some neglected to good use but they don't have enough memory for SunOS Thanks in advance for any There is a free program called 'xkernel' which does just It is by Seth Robertson It takes a sun and boots a limited kernel which allows you to run We converted machines over this semester and the speedup is enormously appreciable I find them faster than an NCD black white XTerminal that we are playing with and a bigger screen to boot As a matter of fact the department just bought some old at an auction to convert Xkernel is available for anonymous ftp from in Xkernel Xkernel is a symlink to the latest version of Xkernel Note that the compiled version which is available is for the sun but compiling to work for a sun should be quite I am not connected with xkernel except as a satisfied installer and user I may be able to answer questions feel free to email Greg Owen Systems Programmer and TA Tufts University Computer Science All transfers are disclaimed by my host name and boss's If you don't like this policy disconnect now